                  <provenance>
                     <p>Copied for <persName type="supplied" key="person_f830">Colonel George William Hamilton (1807-1868)</persName> who served in India from 1823 to 1867 latterly as Commissioner in Delhi. He acquired over a thousand Indian and Persian manuscripts of which 352 were selected after his death for the British Museum. The remainder were purchased in 1868 by <persName type="standard" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/97751058/#Crawford,_Alexander_Crawford_Lindsay,_Earl_of,_1812-1880" key="person_97751058">Alexander Lindsay, 25th Earl of Crawford</persName>.</p>
